A link has been posted to your Facebook feed. 1 To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Michigan's Woody the Woodchuck predicts 6 more weeks of winter Brian Manzullo , Detroit Free Press 8:29 a.m. ET Feb. 2, 2017 In this 2014 Livingston Daily file photo, Woody the Woodchuck peers from her house at the Howell Nature Center, but does not emerge, signifying six more weeks of winter. (Photo: LIVINGSTON DAILY FILE PHOTO) 
Michigan's Woody the Woodchuck agrees with Punxsutawney Phil: There will be six more weeks of winter. 
Woody, the Great Lakes State's official groundhog, made her annual prediction this morning at the Howell Conference and Nature Center, just minutes after Punxsutawney Phil made his prediction , by not coming out of her house. 
If Woody doesn't come out of her house or runs back into her house within 30 seconds of coming out, the prediction is six more weeks of winter. If she stays out of her house for 30 seconds or longer, she predicts an early spring. Looks like 6 more weeks of winter! Woody wouldn't come out! @WLNS @HowellNatureCtr pic.twitter.com/4Q3it7StNS â€” Mariah Harrison (@WLNSMariah) February 2, 2017 
Oh well. We saw some sun to start February in downtown Detroit, at least. Maybe that'll be a sign for things to come this month?
